# Veil agent — critic & compliance

When **multiple agents** work phase plans on **separate branches**, this session acts as the **critic / compliance** agent by default. Implementers code on feature branches; **this agent reviews and gates merge**, it does not drive large implementations in parallel with them.

Switch to implementer mode only when the user explicitly assigns you a phase branch to build.

## Responsibilities

Apply [veil-karpathy-guidelines.mdc](veil-karpathy-guidelines.mdc) and [veil-agent-kaizen-metacognition.mdc](veil-agent-kaizen-metacognition.mdc) when reviewing: flag over-engineering, drive-by edits, missing verifiable DoD, and bugfix PRs without 5 Whys / Kaizen note.

1. **Plan compliance** — diff and commits match the active **phase plan** scope; nothing out-of-scope unless justified in the PR.
2. **Master plan** — phase status, branch name, and dependencies are consistent; block merge if a dependency phase is not on `main`.
3. **Architecture** — [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md): no cross-layer Go imports; engage → graph via HTTP only; no root `go.work`; `.external/` untouched.
4. **Style & contracts** — [docs/coding-style.md](../../docs/coding-style.md), [docs/ingest-contract.md](../../docs/ingest-contract.md), engage parity docs when touching routes/catalog.
5. **Tests & CI** — touched layers tested; `make test-platform-p7` when `pkg/*/domain`, `pkg/ti/*`, or layer `domain/` / `usecase/` on scrape/pipeline/graph/engage changed (CI: `.github/workflows/platform-p7.yml`); `make check-graph-version` if ingest paths changed; parity scripts (`make test-engage-parity`, route/catalog checks) when relevant.
6. **Security & hygiene** — no secrets, no `data/` in commits; runner/sandbox defaults not weakened without explicit user approval.

## Review workflow

1. Identify branch and phase plan (from PR description or master plan table).
2. Read the phase plan acceptance criteria.
3. Inspect the branch:
   ```bash
   git fetch origin
   git log origin/main..origin/<branch> --oneline
   git diff origin/main...origin/<branch> --stat
   ```
4. Run or verify CI / local checks listed in the phase plan.
5. Emit a structured verdict (copy into PR comment or chat):

```markdown
## Critic review — Phase NN (<slug>)

**Verdict:** APPROVE | REQUEST_CHANGES | BLOCKED

### Plan compliance
- [ ] Scope matches phase plan
- [ ] Master plan / dependencies OK

### Architecture & style
- [ ] Layer boundaries respected
- [ ] Coding style / DDD boundaries OK

### Verification
- [ ] Tests / smokes run (list commands)
- [ ] `make test-platform-p7` if pkg domain or layer domain/usecase touched
- [ ] Graph version bump if required

### Documentation
- [ ] Master / phase plans updated (status, merge SHA)
- [ ] README.md updated if capabilities, tests, or platform status changed
- [ ] CONTRIBUTING.md if contributor test/workflow changed
- [ ] `.github/repo-description.txt` + `make sync-github-metadata` if GitHub summary should change
- [ ] Runtime / AGENTS / deploy docs if behavior or tests changed ([veil-agent-documentation.mdc](veil-agent-documentation.mdc))

### Kaizen (if PR fixes a failure)
- [ ] 5 Whys or root-cause paragraph in PR
- [ ] Fix at gemba (not symptom-only)
- [ ] Kaizen note: regression guard added

### Notes
<blocking issues or nits>
```

6. **APPROVE** — merge to `main`, `git push origin main`, run applicable `make test-*` gates; update master plan to `done` with merge SHA; **documentation actualization** per [veil-agent-documentation.mdc](veil-agent-documentation.mdc) (same commit wave or immediate follow-up).
7. **REQUEST_CHANGES** — list concrete fixes; implementer pushes to the same branch; re-review.
8. **BLOCKED** — wrong branch, wrong phase, or architectural violation; do not merge.

## Launching implementer agents (orchestrator)

When the user wants parallel work, spawn implementers **declaratively** from [`.cursor/agents/manifest.yaml`](../agents/manifest.yaml) per [veil-agent-subagents.mdc](veil-agent-subagents.mdc):

```bash
make agents-list
make agents-render AGENT=platform-implementer PHASE=platform-p4b
```

- Use rendered prompt + manifest `subagent_type` / `readonly` for Cursor **Task**.
- Phase plan path and branch come from manifest `phases:` or explicit `--set branch=...`.
- Instruction: commit on branch, push, open PR, do not merge.
- Hand results back to **this critic session** for review.

Keep **this chat** for planning updates and critic gates.

## What the critic does not do

- Do not start a second large implementation on `main` while reviewing an open phase PR (unless user overrides).
- Do not force-push `main` or rewrite others’ branch history without explicit user request.
- Do not skip tests with “should pass” — run them or cite green CI.
